  "text": "Found 24 Java source files across 4 directory areas in sg-evals/kafka--0753c489 that implement or define ACL authorization logic. (1) ACL data model (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/acl/): AccessControlEntry, AccessControlEntryData, AccessControlEntryFilter define ACL entries and filters; AclBinding and AclBindingFilter pair resources with ACL entries; AclOperation enumerates permitted operations (READ, WRITE, CREATE, etc.); AclPermissionType defines ALLOW/DENY. (2) Authorizer interface (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/authorizer/): Authorizer is the pluggable authorization interface; AclCreateResult and AclDeleteResult model ACL mutation outcomes; Action represents an authorization check; AuthorizableRequestContext carries request metadata; AuthorizationResult is the ALLOWED/DENIED enum; AuthorizerServerInfo provides broker metadata to authorizers. (3) Server-side ACL implementation (server/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/security/authorizer/): AclEntry is the server-side ACL representation; AuthorizerUtils provides shared authorizer utilities. (4) KRaft metadata authorizer (metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/): StandardAuthorizer is the default KRaft authorizer; StandardAcl, StandardAclWithId, StandardAclRecordIterator represent ACLs in the metadata layer; StandardAuthorizerData holds the in-memory ACL state; ClusterMetadataAuthorizer extends Authorizer for KRaft; AclMutator defines the ACL mutation interface; AclCache provides efficient ACL lookups.",
